    <ns0:description descriptionType="Abstract">The Normalized Symmetric cumulant $NSC(n,m)$ results as a function of multiplicity ($N_{trk}^{offline}$) in pPb collisions at $\sqrt{s_{NN}}$ = 8.16 TeV. The results are normalized by $\left&lt;(v_2^{\text{sub}})^{2}\right&gt; \, \left&lt;(v_3^{\text{sub}})^{2}\right&gt;$ and $\left&lt;(v_2^{\text{sub}})^{2}\right&gt; \, \left&lt;(v_4^{\text{sub}})^{2}\right&gt;$ from two-particle correlations.</ns0:description>
